rows.label: tlk70000073_03_msg0001
rows.name:
I went into town to pick up some
things and who do I bump into? Iris.
Grabbed my shoulder in the street.

rows.label: tlk70000073_03_msg0002
rows.name:
I thought that was it for me, my cover
blown. But he bought the whole woman
disguise thing and let me go...

rows.label: tlk70000073_03_msg0003
rows.name:
Seems he still doesn't
believe I'm dead. Thinks
I'm hiding away somewhere.

rows.label: tlk70000073_03_msg0004
rows.name:
I told him to forget about Meknes. But
then he flipped a lid right there in
public, told me to mind my business.

rows.label: tlk70000073_03_msg0005
rows.name:
Like a fool, I almost shouted
back, "I'm him! It is my
business!"... But then I didn't.

rows.label: tlk70000073_03_msg0006
rows.name:
That was the moment I realised that
Meknes was well and truly gone.

rows.label: tlk70000073_03_msg0007
rows.name:
Looks like I'll have to come up with
a new name... Excuse the tears, there
must be something in my eye...
